{{Infobox Hieroglyphen
|NAME = <hiero>G40-G1-N35-Aa1:N35:O34-M23-G43</hiero> <br/> Pa-en-Chonsu <br/> ''P3-n-ḫnsw'' <br/> ''The (Month) of {{ill|Chonsu|de|Chons|qq=draft|12=draft}}''
|NAME2 = <hiero>N11:Z1 S-N35B N5</hiero> <br/> abed-1 schemu <br/>''3bd-1 šmw'' <br/> ''First Month of the {{ill|Season_of_the_Harvest|lt=Shemu|de|Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest|lt=Schemu|qq=draft|12=draft}} Period''
}}

'''Pa-en-Chonsu''' ({{ill|Ancient Greek language|de|Griechische Sprache|qq=draft|12=draft}} '''Pachon'''; {{ill|Coptic language|de|Koptische Sprache|qq=draft|12=draft}} '''Paschons'''; بشنس '''Baschans''') was the {{ill|Ancient Egyptian calendar|de|Ägyptischer Kalender|qq=draft|12=draft}} name for the first month of the {{ill|Season_of_the_Harvest|lt=Shemu|de|Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest|lt=Schemu|qq=draft|12=draft}} season and represented the period from early {{ill|March|de|März|qq=draft|12=draft}} to early {{ill|April|de|April|qq=draft|12=draft}}. 

== Background ==
=== Position in the Calendar ===
{{ill|Alan Gardiner|de|Alan Gardiner|qq=draft|12=draft}} as well as {{ill|Richard Anthony Parker|de|Richard Anthony Parker|qq=draft|12=draft}} suggest that Pa-en-Chonsu changed its seasonal position throughout the history of the calendar.

From the {{ill|Predynastic Egypt|de|Prädynastik (Ägypten)|qq=draft|12=draft}} until the end of the {{ill|Middle Kingdom of Egypt|de|Mittleres Reich (Ägypten)|qq=draft|12=draft}}, Pa-en-Chonsu was originally the tenth month of the {{ill|Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar|lt=`Sothic calendar|de|Mondkalender (Altes Ägypten)|1=Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar#Der spätere Mondkalender|qq=draft|12=draft}} under the name {{ill|Chonsu (month)|de|Chonsu (Monat)|qq=draft|lt=Chonsu|12=draft}}. By the time of the {{ill|19th Dynasty of Egypt|de|19. Dynastie|qq=draft|12=draft}}, during the {{ill|New Kingdom of Egypt|de|Neues Reich|qq=draft|12=draft}}, it had shifted to become the first month of the {{ill|Season_of_the_Harvest|lt=Shemu|de|Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest|lt=Schemu|qq=draft|12=draft}} season.

=== Beginning of the Flax Harvest ===
The lunar calendar month Pa-en-Chonsu is documented in records from the {{ill|12th Dynasty of Egypt|de|12. Dynastie|qq=draft|12=draft}} as the month of Chonsu, marking the beginning of the {{ill|Flax harvest (Ancient Egypt)|de|Flachsernte (Altes Ägypten)|qq=draft|lt=Flax harvest|12=draft}}. In administrative records, it was associated with the first "work of picking out" during what was then the {{ill|Achet|de|Achet#Datierungen|1=Season_of_the_Inundation#Months|lt=Achet|qq=draft|12=draft}} season’s fourth month (February/Early March).
== See Also ==
* [[:en:Gezer calendar|Gezer calendar]]

== References ==
* {{ill|Rolf Krauss|de|Rolf Krauss|qq=draft|12=draft}}: ''Sothis- und Monddaten. Studien zur astronomischen und technischen Chronologie Altägyptens'' (= ''Hildesheimer ägyptologische Beiträge.'' Band 20). Gerstenberg, Hildesheim 1985, {{Falsche ISBN|3-8067-8086-X}}.
* {{ill|Richard Anthony Parker|de|Richard Anthony Parker|qq=draft|12=draft}}: ''The calendars of ancient Egypt'' (= ''Studies in ancient oriental civilization.'' Band 26). Unchanged reprint of the 1950 Chicago edition; University Press, Chicago (Ill) 1979. 
* {{ill|Siegfried Schott|de|Siegfried Schott|qq=draft|12=draft}}: ''Altägyptische Festdaten'' (= ''Abhandlungen der Akademie der Wissenschaften und der Literatur/ Geistes- und sozialwissenschaftliche Klasse.'' Band 10). Steiner, Mainz 1950. 

