|NAME = <hiero>G40-G1-N35-Aa1:N35:O34-M23-G43</hiero> <br/> Pa-en-Chonsu <br/> ''P3-n-ḫnsw'' <br/> ''The (Month) of {{ill|Khonsu|en|Khonsu|WD=Q190521|lt=Chonsu|1=Khonsu}}''
|NAME2 = <hiero>N11:Z1 S-N35B N5</hiero> <br/> abed-1 schemu <br/>''3bd-1 šmw'' <br/> ''First Month of the {{ill|Season of the Harvest|en|Season of the Harvest|WD=Q1248622|lt=Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest}} Period''
}}

'''Pa-en-Chonsu''' ({{ill|Greek language|en|Greek language|WD=Q9129|lt=Ancient Greek language|1=Greek language}} '''Pachon'''; {{ill|Coptic language|en|Coptic language|WD=Q36155|lt=Coptic language|1=Coptic language}} '''Paschons'''; بشنس '''Baschans''') was the {{ill|Egyptian calendar|en|Egyptian calendar|WD=Q254101|lt=Ancient Egyptian calendar|1=Egyptian calendar}} name for the first month of the {{ill|Season of the Harvest|en|Season of the Harvest|WD=Q1248622|lt=Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest}} season and represented the period from early {{ill|March|en|March|WD=Q110|lt=March|1=March}} to early {{ill|April|en|April|WD=Q118|lt=April|1=April}}. 

== Background ==
=== Position in the Calendar ===
{{ill|Alan Gardiner|en|Alan Gardiner|WD=Q441060|lt=Alan Gardiner|1=Alan Gardiner}} as well as {{ill|Richard Anthony Parker|en|Richard Anthony Parker|WD=Q2148992|lt=Richard Anthony Parker|1=Richard Anthony Parker}} suggest that Pa-en-Chonsu changed its seasonal position throughout the history of the calendar.

From the {{ill|Predynastic Egypt|de|Prädynastik (Ägypten)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Predynastic Egypt|qq=|WD=Q714601|1=Predynastic Egypt}} until the end of the {{ill|Middle Kingdom of Egypt|en|Middle Kingdom of Egypt|WD=Q191324|lt=Middle Kingdom of Egypt|1=Middle Kingdom of Egypt}}, Pa-en-Chonsu was originally the tenth month of the {{ill|Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar|lt=`Sothic calendar|de|Mondkalender (Altes Ägypten)|1=Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Ancient Egyptian Lunar Calendar#Der spätere Mondkalender|qq=|WD=Q1944246}} under the name {{ill|Chonsu (month)|de|Chonsu (Monat)|lt=Chonsu|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chonsu (month)|qq=|WD=Q259644|1=Chonsu (month)}}. By the time of the {{ill|Nineteenth Dynasty of Egypt|en|Nineteenth Dynasty of Egypt|WD=Q157956|lt=19th Dynasty of Egypt|1=Nineteenth Dynasty of Egypt}}, during the {{ill|New Kingdom of Egypt|en|New Kingdom of Egypt|WD=Q180568|lt=New Kingdom of Egypt|1=New Kingdom of Egypt}}, it had shifted to become the first month of the {{ill|Season of the Harvest|en|Season of the Harvest|WD=Q1248622|lt=Schemu|1=Season of the Harvest}} season.

=== Beginning of the Flax Harvest ===
The lunar calendar month Pa-en-Chonsu is documented in records from the {{ill|Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt|en|Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt|WD=Q719639|lt=12th Dynasty of Egypt|1=Twelfth Dynasty of Egypt}} as the month of Chonsu, marking the beginning of the {{ill|Flax harvest (Ancient Egypt)|de|Flachsernte (Altes Ägypten)|lt=Flax harvest|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Flax harvest (Ancient Egypt)|qq=|WD=Q1426240|1=Flax harvest (Ancient Egypt)}}. In administrative records, it was associated with the first "work of picking out" during what was then the {{ill|Achet|de|Achet#Datierungen|1=Season of the Inundation|lt=Achet|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Achet|13=User:Immanuelle/Season_of_the_Inundation#Months|qq=|WD=Q770568}} season’s fourth month (February/Early March).
